function [x,y] = VecP2V(s,d)%---------------------------------------------------------------------------%function [x,y] = VecP2V(s,d)%VECP2V - convert vector speed and direction to true vector components%Vectors are reported in  %  oceanographic convention which means the vector points in the direction the water/wind is going, respectively.%%INPUT% s = speed% d = direction (ocean convention, toward direction, 0 deg = North, 90 deg = E)%OUTPUT% x,y are vector components, x = east, y = north, TO direction%% USES SUBROUTINES:% CompassCheck() -- puts the input heading to [0-360) range.%%reynolds 070924%---------------------------------------------------------------------------d2r = pi / 180;d = CompassCheck(d);x = s .* sin(d2r * d);y = s  .* cos(d2r * d);return